<TEXT>
at least 100 people most of them poor 
laborers died and more than 200 others were battling for their 
lives after drinking homemade liquor in the western city of baroda 
news reports said monday 
press trust of india and said at least 100 of the 251 people 
hospitalized after drinking the illicit brew saturday were in 
critical condition united news of india said survival chances were 
bleak for virtually all the patients 
both news agencies said the death toll was at least 100 and was 
expected to rise 
the mass poisoning in gujarat the only indian state where sale 
of alcohol is banned was the countrys worst known liquor poisoning 
case the news agencies said many victims are likely to go blind if 
they live doctors treating the patients said according to united 
news of india 
press trust quoted doctors as saying some of the victims could 
have been saved if they had sought treatment earlier it said many 
victims became dizzy and fell into stupors after drinking the 
illegal brew in the city 560 miles southwest of new delhi 
united news said police arrested three people who had supplied 
the liquor a son of one supplier and the son of a prominent local 
politician were among those killed by the poisonous brew it said 
gujarats chief minister amarsinh chaudhary ordered an 
investigation and promised drastic action against the police 
officials who failed to avert the tragedy the times of india 
reported 
the newspaper said most of the victims were poor laborers who 
bought the liquor saturday morning after receiving their monthly 
wages the first deaths were reported about midnight saturday it 
added 
as news of the first deaths emerged police fanned out across 
baroda with loudspeakers blaring warnings that anyone who had 
consumed the liquor should seek medical help immediately 
the liquor known locally as lattha is made from industrial 
spirits and methyl alcohol 
about 300 people have died in about seven illicit liquor 
tragedies in gujarat during the last decade uni said two of the 
previous cases occurred in baroda with others reported in ahmedabad 
and surat 
</TEXT>
