<TEXT>
today is monday march 6 the 65th day of 1989 there are 300 
days left in the year 
todays highlight in history 
on march 6 1836 the alamo in san antonio texas fell to 
mexican forces after a 13day siege all 187 defenders of the 
mission compound including davy crockett and james bowie were 
killed 
on this date 
in 1806 poet elizabeth barrett browning was born in durham 
england 
in 1834 the city of york in upper canada was incorporated as 
toronto 
in 1853 verdis opera la traviata premiered in venice italy 
in 1857 in its dred scott decision the us supreme court 
held that scott a slave could not sue for his freedom in a federal 
court 
in 1933 a nationwide bank holiday declared by president franklin 
d roosevelt went into effect 
in 1935 retired supreme court justice oliver wendell holmes jr 
died in washington 
in 1944 us bombers staged a daylight raid against berlin 
during world war ii 
in 1957 the former british african colonies of the gold coast 
and togoland became the independent state of ghana 
in 1967 the daughter of josef stalin svetlana alliluyeva 
appeared at the us embassy in india and announced her intention to 
defect to the west 
in 1981 walter cronkite signed off for the last time as 
anchorman of the cbs evening news 
in 1982 authorphilosopher ayn rand died in new york at age 77 
in 1983 in a case that drew much notoriety a woman in new 
bedford mass said she had been gangraped atop a pool table in a 
tavern called big dans four men were later convicted in connection 
with the case 
in 1983 the proenvironment antinuclear greens party won 
seats in west germanys lower house of parliament for the first time 
in 1987 189 people died when water rushed through the open bow 
doors of the herald of free enterprise causing the british 
ferry to capsize off the belgian port of zeebrugge 
ten years ago a jury was empaneled in oklahoma city in the case 
of nuclear plant worker karen g silkwood who was contaminated with 
plutonium through what silkwoods family charged was the negligence 
of her employer kerrmcgee corp shortly before her death in a 
1974 car crash although the jury ruled against kerrmcgee an 
appeals court in 1985 ordered a retrial 
five years ago democratic presidential hopeful gary hart won 
vermonts preference vote by a wide margin over walter f mondale 
following victories over mondale in the new hampshire primary and 
maine caucuses 
one year ago the board of trustees at gallaudet university in 
washington dc the worlds only liberal arts college for the deaf 
chose a hearing woman elisabeth ann zinser school president over 
two deaf candidates outraged students shut down the campus forcing 
zinsers ouster and the selection of a deaf president in her place 
