<TEXT>
once congressional pages together paul 
kanjorski and bill emerson both realized their dream of being 
elected to the us house 
as if that were not unusual enough both also were witnesses to 
the rarest of events an attack by gunmen on the congress of the 
united states 
kanjorski dpa and emerson rmo stood together on the house 
floor last wednesday to mark the 35th anniversary of an event they 
said will always seem fresh in their minds 
the two were 16yearold pages and roommates on march 1 1954 
the day that four neatly dressed puerto ricans walked into the 
public galleries unfurled a flag shouted free puerto rico and 
began shooting randomly from large automatic pistols 
house speaker joseph w martin jr who had been counting heads 
in a quorum call on a bill dealing with migrant laborers banged 
the gavel 
a few congressmen fell bleeding some raced for the doors some 
hid under the tables 
as one who has never been particularly ageconscious i stand 
in awe of the fact that this event occurred 35 years ago and i 
remember it as though it were yesterday emerson said last week 
kanjorski had just gotten out of his seat on the democratic side 
in the rear of the chamber when the shooting started 
when the shots started to be fired they sounded like 
firecrackers going off kanjorski said last week there were a 
lot of them and they were differentsounding because there were 
several weapons that were being used the only thing that made it 
clear they werent firecrackers is that i got sprinkled with some of 
the marble that flaked off 
emerson thought the noise was firecrackers too but when i 
looked up i could see fire coming out of the end of the barrels of 
those guns 
wounded were reps alvin bentley rmich ben jensen riowa 
george fallon dmd kenneth roberts dala and clifford davis 
dtenn all recovered 
before it was over a photographer snapped a picture of kanjorski 
and emerson carrying one of them off on a stretcher 
as bad as the moment was the news photo gave kanjorski and 
emerson temporary celebrity status among their peers and linked 
them together in time 
all through our lives we have been very close friends 
kanjorski said he classified the odds of both becoming congressmen 
as remote even though he said both dreamed about the 
possibility 
one of the attackers died in 1979 and the other three were given 
presidential clemency the same year after 25 years in prison 
emerson was elected to congress in 1980 kanjorski four years 
later 
i might say it was a great pleasure for me personally when my 
