<TEXT>
a reseacher bitten by a deadly viper has 
stabilized and wont receive antivenins obtained from iran england 
and the soviet union with help from the white house unless his 
condition worsens doctors say 
william e haast 78 remained in serious but stable condition 
today at the university of utah health sciences center spokesman 
john dwan said sunday haast had been moved out of intensive care 
into a regular nursing unit 
his condition has not changed dwan said hes resting 
comfortably and hes had lots of friends visiting him 
haast likely would remain hospitalized for at least two to three 
more weeks dwan said he checked into the hospital wednesday 
haast director of the miami serpentarium laboratories at the 
universitys research park was bitten tuesday on the left hand by a 
pakistani pit viper also known as a sawscaled viper 
haast has been bitten 148 times by snakes and is immune to the 
venom of dozens but he had no immunity to the viper it is one of 
1000 poisonous snakes kept at his lab where venom is extracted for 
research and the manufacture of antivenins 
the serpentologists case drew the attention of stephen studdert 
special assistant to president bush who coordinated the acquisition 
of antivenins from the three countries and expedited their shipment 
to utah all the shipments had arrived by sunday 
none have been used because there are sometimes serious 
reactions to antivenins and doctors dont want to give them to him 
unless they have to dwan explained the reactions could include 
lung and kidney problems he said 
nevertheless dwan said we want to express our appreciation to 
everyone who has worked so hard in obtaining the antivenins 
the vipers venom attacks its victims ability to produce 
fibrinogen an element of blood that regulates coagulation a lack 
of fibrinogen can cause uncontrolled bleeding 
haasts fibrinogen level was near zero wednesday doctors were 
replacing it with transfusions and it appeared haasts body had 
begun to produce the substance 
his fibrinogen level improved to about onethird of normal by 
sunday still dangerously low dwan said 
haast had been treated earlier with antivenins from the san diego 
zoo and from a lab in los angeles but they did not work as well as 
expected 
studdert said the iranian government apparently did not interfere 
with the shipment of the antivenin despite the strained relations 
with the united states iranian leader ayatollah khomeini has often 
called the united states the great satan 
