1500 yards off a littleused shoreline about 15 miles from honolulu 
and its famed waikiki beach 
cleanup crews spent their third day removing oil from a twomile 
stretch of coastline sunday 
the us fish and wildlife service said there were no reports of 
birds or marine life being harmed by the oil 
exxon shipping co president frank j iarossi said the company 
will spend whatever is needed to clean the beaches and ocean 
despite the wind and seas the exxon houston was within safety 
standards for unloading its cargo of alaska north slope crude oil at 
the hawaiian independent refinery iarossi said 
about 25200 gallons of crude oil spilled when floating hoses at 
the mooring buoy separated and about 8400 gallons of fuel oil 
spilled from a ruptured tank when the ship ran aground according to 
revised estimates saturday by coast guard officials earlier 
estimates were that 117000 gallons of oil had spilled 
the tanker floated free of the reef on the rising tide friday 
night after its ballast water was pumped out 
</TEXT>
