was at 108 in january down from 1112 in december it was the 
largest monthtomonth drop since a similar decline in january 1988 
the new january number means that a family earning the median 
income of 32207 annually had 8 percent more income than needed to 
qualify for a mortgage covering 80 percent of the purchase price of 
a medianpriced home 
the median price for an existing home in january was 91500 
meaning half the homes sold for more and half for less januarys 
median was up 2800 from the previous month 
the mortgage rate used to calculate the index rose to 961 
percent in january from 959 percent representing a composite of 
fixed and adjustable rates 
