provocative acts 
the makeshift harbor at jiye has been the main sea outlet for the 
druze community a moslem sect based mainly in the chouf mountains 
since they captured it from the christians in 1985 
a defense ministry communique said foreign ships heading for 
lebanon have been warned not to enter any of the militiacontrolled 
harbors along the mediterranean countrys 110mile coastline 
the ban was ordered sunday by gen michel aoun who heads the 
christian military cabinet vying for power with hoss syrianbacked 
government 
it was part of aouns campaign to restore state authority eroded 
by 14 years of civil war in which christian and moslem militias took 
over many government functions 
the militias use the ports to bring in arms and supplies as well 
as imported goods sold in the areas they control depriving the 
state treasury of an estimated 100 million a year in customs duties 
were not forcibly shutting militia harbors or blockading them 
we are merely blocking foreign ships from going there a 
defense ministry spokesman said on condition of anonymity 
if a ship insists on violating the ban it will be seized and 
forced to sail into beirut port to question its captain before 
beginning legal procedures said the spokesman 
he listed five legal ports beirut jounieh and tripoli north of 
the capital and sidon and tyre to the south 
to supervise the new ban aoun revived a maritime authority made 
up of representatives from the public works ministry the navy air 
force police and the customs department 
hoss said monday that the ban could undermine the positive mood 
that has lately emerged about a possible end to lebanons plight 
he was referring to mediation efforts by an arab league committee 
set up in january to help resolve a constitutional crisis that has 
