<TEXT>
europes 29th ariane rocket lifted 
off successfully monday from this south american launch center and 
put a japanese and a european satellite into orbit 
the launch had been scheduled for feb 28 but was postponed 
because of a strike by technicians it was rescheduled for saturday 
but delayed again when high winds caused two umbilical cables to 
disconnect as the gantry was being pulled away 
seventeen minutes 41 seconds after liftoff at 829 pm the 
ariane 4 attained orbit and after seven more minutes it had 
released the two satellites ariane 4 is the most powerful launcher 
in the ariane series 
put into orbit were jcsat1 a japanese commercial communication 
satellite and mop1 a european meteorological satellite 
the jdsat1 built by hughes aircraft co of los angeles for the 
japanese communication satellite co is japans first commercial 
communication satellite 
mop1 is the fourth weather satellite for the european space 
agency it will send weather pictures every half hour to stations on 
earth 
it was the agencys second launch this year and the 11th straight 
successful operation 
the first ariane rocket an ariane 1 was launched a decade ago 
the agency has had four failed flights since its rocket became 
operational 
the last failure was in 1986 and resulted in a delay in the 
program of more than a yearlaunches resumed in september 1987 
