plans by pilots for nearly all us airlines to 
strictly fly by the rule book starting tuesday could cause lengthy 
flight delays especially where there is heavy traffic and bad 
weather according to aviation experts and pilots 
the air line pilots association announced the action by its 
40000 members as a show of support for 8500 striking eastern 
airlines machinists union members and the eastern pilots and flight 
stewardesses who have refused to cross the picket lines 
pilots in announcing the action said it would not amount to a 
slowdown because they would simply be following procedures 
taking the longer option when there are two or more safe options 
available 
the primary impact could come if pilots rely on instrument 
landing procedures when they could use visual procedures said faa 
spokesman john leyden 
but leyden said it was impossible to tell how much the pilots 
action would affect overall air travel he said in some instances 
the impact might be minimal and in areas where weather is bad and 
traffic heavy it could be greater 
