available to the public in about three years it would grow to only 
about four inches need little or no fertilizer and pesticides and 
crowd out less desirable grasses 
engelke wants it to be called prairie buffalo grass because 
it reminds him of the rippling windblown grass crossed by prairie 
schooners 
