buyers snapped up the 1988 burley crop 
across the eightstate belt with gross sales up almost 50 million 
pounds over the previous year 
kentucky burley farmers led the way in both production and price 
again this year selling a total of 3803 million pounds for an 
average price of 16145 per pound 
the lowest statewide average was registered in west virginia 
where the huntington market sold 28 million pounds for an average 
of 15368 a pound 
gross sales for the 1988 crop throughout the area known as the 
burley belt totaled 5307 million pounds compared with 484 million 
pounds the year before 
in addition the average price per pound increased 47 cents a 
pound from 15634 in 198788 to 16104 
it looks to me like the tobacco program the tobacco situation 
is as good as it has been for a long time said danny mckinney 
executive secretary of the burley tobacco growers cooperative 
association 
the 1988 crop was rescued from last summers drought by rains 
beginning in midjuly and was far superior to the previous years 
crop in 1987 a dry autumn curing season left much of the burley 
brittle and undesirable 
the burley selling season concluded last week burley is a 
thinleaved lightcolored tobacco usually containing less nicotine 
than the darkcolored varieties 
