<TEXT>
paraguay has reapplied to join the 96nation 
general agreement on tariffs and trade the main pact setting rules 
for world trade a gatt source said monday 
the source speaking on condition of anonymity said a paraguyan 
delegate brought his nations bid to a regular meeting monday of 
gatts governing council which is open to all members 
after the overthrow of longtime military strongman alfredo 
stroessner last month paraguays new government had notified the 
gatt administration that it wants to pursue its bid to join which 
it abandoned in 1974 
gatt has agreed to consider the request the source said 
reaching a decision seems likely to take months if not years 
asked whether the timing of the bid was related to the new 
governments coming to power the gatt source said only that 
paraguay already had indicated renewed interest in joining for about 
a year 
gatt is an agreement promoting free trade and also a forum for 
negotiations and resolution of trade disputes gatt sets mutual 
privileges and obligations an attempt at expanding their scope 
aimed at further freeing global commerce is currently underway in a 
fouryear round of world trade talks due to wind up in 1990 
</TEXT>
