since coming to eastern airlines as president 2 
years ago phil bakes has insisted he has firm plans to pull the 
carrier out of its 10year financial tailspin 
the crippling strike that continued in its third day today 
indicates his employees dont really believe him 
instead union leaders call bakes one of the continental 
crew the executive team that helped texas air corp chairman 
frank lorenzo turn continental airlines into a cheaplabor 
predominantly nonunion company 
its lorenzo and his unionbuster image that has galvanized 
easterns workers who believe his priorites are attacking organized 
labor and milking cash out of eastern 
by all the actions theyve already taken its clear where hes 
taking the airline pilots union spokesman ron cole said sunday 
after bakes made a nationally televised plea for pilots to cross 
machinists union picket lines and return to work he bakes is 
trying to deflect the issue away from frank lorenzo 
what were seeing here is a remake of the continental movie 
youve got the same players and frank lorenzo as the script writer 
and director cole said but this time the first act has been 
different 
