grain and soybean futures prices closed mostly 
higher monday on the chicago board of trade with the wheat market 
posting solid gains amid weather concerns and new export activity 
the key winterwheat states of kansas oklahoma texas and 
nebraska received far less precipitation over the weekend than many 
traders had expected spurring brisk buying monday of newcrop wheat 
futures contracts for delivery in july or later 
wheat for nearterm delivery was supported by reports that china 
was seeking to buy 400000 metric tons of us wheat at subsidized 
prices for april or may delivery 
the soybean complex was boosted by heavy speculative buying of 
soybean meal futures although analysts could cite no new 
supplyanddemand developments to account for the late surge 
corn futures finished narrowly mixed 
